Why the "Ignore" Logic Matters
In modern development, a node_modules folder or a .git directory can contain thousands of files. If you run a tree command without ignores, your terminal will often hang while it scrolls through thousands of lines of metadata you don't actually want to see.

The -u (unfilter) flag is your "emergency" option for when you actually need to debug a git hook or a local package dependency, but keeping it off by default keeps your lt output lightning-fast.

